{"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone": {"Harry James Potter, an 11-year-old boy, lives with his cruel aunt and uncle, Vernon and Petunia Dursley, and their spoiled son Dudley.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "Unbeknownst to Harry, he is a wizard, and his parents, Lily and James Potter, were powerful wizards killed by the dark wizard Lord Voldemort.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "However, when Voldemort tried to kill Harry as a baby, the spell backfired, leaving the dark wizard nearly destroyed and leaving Harry with a lightning-shaped scar on his forehead.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "On his 11th birthday, Harry receives his first letter from Rubeus Hagrid, informing him that he has been accepted to attend Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "Hagrid reveals that Harry's parents were famous wizards and that he survived an attack by Voldemort.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "Harry learns that he will attend Hogwarts, a magical school where young witches and wizards learn magic, and that he will make new friends and discover his own potential.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "At Hogwarts, Harry befriends Ron Weasley and Hermione Granger, and they begin to uncover more information about the elusive Philosopher's Stone, an object with incredible powers, including the ability to turn any metal into pure gold and produce the Elixir of Life.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "As they search for answers, they discover that the Philosopher's Stone is being protected by magical obstacles and challenges designed to prevent anyone from obtaining it.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "The trio faces various challenges, including a life-sized wizard's chess game and a potion riddle created by Professor Snape.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "Through their bravery, resourcefulness, and teamwork, they ultimately reach the final chamber where the Philosopher's Stone is hidden.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "In the final confrontation, Harry faces Professor Quirrell, who is now entirely consumed by Voldemort's spirit.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "Harry, refusing to give up, uses the power of his mother's love to defeat Quirrell and prevent Voldemort from obtaining the Philosopher's Stone.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "In the aftermath, Dumbledore explains to Harry that the love and protection he carries will guide him in the future, making him the only one capable of truly confronting Voldemort.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "The end of the school year is an emotional and reflective moment for Harry and his friends, Ron and Hermione, as they look back on their first year at Hogwarts with a mixture of relief and pride.": {"questions": null, "types": null}}}